      "**Output:**\n**web_search_prime_result_summary:** [{\"text\": [{\"title\": \"Air Launches as Public Preview – A New Wave of Dev ...\", \"link\": \"https://blog.jetbrains.com/air/2026/03/air-launches-as-public-preview-a-new-wave-of-dev-tooling-built-on-26-years-of-experience/\", \"content\": \"It's available to developers with a JetBrains AI subscription or thos...\n                                                Based on the search results, here's what I found about JetBrains Air and its public preview:\n\n## JetBrains Air - Agentic IDE Public Preview\n\n### Overview\nJetBrains has launched **Air** as a public preview - a new \"agentic\" development environment built on 26 years of JetBrains' IDE experience. Unlike traditional IDEs, Air is designed around AI agents rather than the editor itself.\n\n### Key Features\n\n1. **Agent-Centric Architecture**: Air is built to orchestrate multiple AI coding agents concurrently, allowing them to run tasks in parallel\n\n2. **Multi-Agent Orchestration**: You can delegate coding tasks to multiple AI agents that work simultaneously, with a user interface for managing multiple agent vendors\n\n3. **Built on Fleet**: Air is built on top of the codebase from JetBrains Fleet (which appears to have been abandoned/repurposed for this project)\n\n4. **ACP Support & BYOK**: It supports Agent Communication Protocol (ACP) and Bring Your Own Key (BYOK) functionality\n\n### Availability\n\n- **Current Status**: Public Preview (launched March 2026)\n- **Platform Support**: Currently only **macOS version is available**, with Windows and Linux versions promised later\n- **Access Requirements**: Available to developers with:\n  - A JetBrains AI subscription, OR\n  - Existing subscriptions to agent providers (except Anthropic) and API access\n\n### Key Differentiator\nUnlike traditional IDEs where the editor is central, Air is designed as an \"agentic\" environment where AI agents are the primary focus, acting as an orchestration layer for multiple AI coding assistants working together.\n\nFor more information, you can visit the [official Air website](https://air.dev/) or read the [JetBrains blog announcement](https://blog.jetbrains.com/air/2026/03/air-launches-as-public-preview-a-new-wave-of-dev-tooling-built-on-26-years-of-experience/)."
